        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Park the vehicle on a flat, level surface and chock the wheels to prevent property damage
                        and/or personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Compressed air and open dry brushing should never be used for cleaning brake assemblies.
                        Exposure to airborne brake dust can cause serious or fatal diseases.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set the parking brake, jack up the front axle and support with jack stands.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the front tire and brake drum.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the hub cap assembly and drain lubricant into an appropriate container for
                    disposal.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cotter pin, slotted bearing adjusting nut, outer wheel bearing then slide the hub
                    off the spindle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove brake shoes. Refer to CTS-5060, in Group 04 of the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual
                    for detailed instructions.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the slack adjuster from the brake chamber and brake cam.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the brake cam from the brake cam tube.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tie strap retaining the ABS sensor wire to the brake cam tube and remove the
                    brake cam tube from the brake spider/backing plate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the ABS sensor from the brake spider/backing plate.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the seven mounting bolts that hold the brake spider/backing plate to the axle
                    flange and remove the brake spider/backing plate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new brake spider/backing plate.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the spider/backing plate mounting bolts (5/8 inch-Grade 8) to 175 to 190 ft-lbs.
                    (237 to 258 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the brake components. Refer to CTS-5060, in Group 04 of the CTS-5000 Master
                    Service Manual for detailed instructions.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install plastic tie strap to secure ABS sensor wire to the brake cam housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the wheel seal in the hub assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the hub assembly, outer wheel bearing, slotted nut and cotter pin.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the hub cap and fill with lubricant to the proper level.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the brake drum and tire.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the wheel bearing adjustment and bearing end play following the procedure in
                    CTS-5136S, in Group 02 of the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify proper brake and slack adjuster adjustment.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the ABS sensor is properly adjusted.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat the procedure for the opposite side.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
